The paper discusses spectrum sharing in 5G networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of matching theory algorithms to resolve conflicting preferences of spectrum providers and users suggests a game-theoretic approach (cs.GT). The evaluation of performance using Monte Carlo simulations suggests a focus on simulation and modeling (cs.SI) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
